HEADWORD: Mandelic
<hw>Man*del"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>mandel</ets> almond.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to
an acid first obtained from benzoic aldehyde (oil of better almonds), as
a white crystalline substance; -- called also <xex>phenyl glycolic
acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

